          <h3 class="lp-why-title">All Brands Welcome</h3>
          <p class="lp-why-body">Asus, Acer, Lenovo, HP, Dell, Toshiba, MSI, Razer, Samsung, LG, Huawei, and every Chromebook brand — we service them all. You don't need a brand-specific shop in Winnipeg. Walk in with whatever laptop you have and we'll tell you exactly what's wrong and what it costs before we start.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="lp-why-card">
          <div class="lp-why-icon-wrap">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lp-why-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><rect x="2" y="6" width="20" height="12" rx="2"/><path d="M22 10H2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="lp-why-title">Upgrades That Transform Old Laptops</h3>
          <p class="lp-why-body">Replacing a spinning hard drive with an NVMe SSD is the single most impactful laptop upgrade available — it can make a 5-year-old laptop boot in seconds and feel completely new. We also perform RAM upgrades on laptops with upgradeable memory slots. An SSD upgrade often costs less than buying a new laptop and delivers a better result.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="lp-why-card">
          <div class="lp-why-icon-wrap">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lp-why-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><rect x="4" y="4" width="16" height="16" rx="2" ry="2"/><rect x="9" y="9" width="6" height="6"/><line x1="9" y1="1" x2="9" y2="4"/><line x1="15" y1="1" x2="15" y2="4"/><line x1="9" y1="20" x2="9" y2="23"/><line x1="15" y1="20" x2="15" y2="23"/><line x1="20" y1="9" x2="23" y2="9"/><line x1="20" y1="14" x2="23" y2="14"/><line x1="1" y1="9" x2="4" y2="9"/><line x1="1" y1="14" x2="4" y2="14"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="lp-why-title">Component-Level Motherboard Repair</h3>
          <p class="lp-why-body">Most laptop shops in Winnipeg refuse motherboard repairs or quote a full board replacement. We perform component-level diagnostics and micro-soldering to identify and repair specific failures — charging IC chips, power mosfets, broken USB controllers, and display connector damage — often at a fraction of the cost of a board swap.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="lp-why-card">
          <div class="lp-why-icon-wrap">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lp-why-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/><polyline points="9 12 11 14 15 10"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="lp-why-title">Warranty on Every Repair</h3>
          <p class="lp-why-body">Screen repairs carry a 30-day to lifetime warranty depending on part tier. Battery replacements include a 90-day warranty. All other repairs carry a lifetime warranty on parts and labour. We run free diagnostics before any repair and give you a clear upfront quote — no surprises.</p>
