  <section class="lp-pricing-context-section">
    <div class="lp-container">
      <div class="lp-pricing-context-content">
        <p>Laptop repair costs vary significantly by brand, model, and repair type — a screen replacement on a budget Acer Aspire costs considerably less than a Dell XPS OLED panel replacement, and a simple battery swap is almost always cost-effective regardless of brand. <a href="https://www.ifixit.com/Search?query=laptop+repair+guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">iFixit's laptop repair guides</a> rate repairability across brands, showing why some laptops are significantly cheaper to repair than others.</p>
        <p>Many customers are surprised when a laptop screen replacement costs nearly as much as a budget replacement laptop. This is most common with premium ultrabooks and gaming laptops — the displays are proprietary, high-resolution, and expensive to source. We always provide an honest comparison of repair cost versus current device value before starting.</p>
        <p>If the repair cost exceeds your laptop's current market value, we'll explain that clearly and walk you through alternatives — including data recovery and transfer to a new machine, or trade-in value toward a replacement. We'd rather give you the right advice than take money for a repair that doesn't make financial sense. See also: <a href="/repairs/macbook">MacBook repair in Winnipeg</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

