  <section class="lp-faq-section" id="faq">
    <div class="lp-container">
      <div class="lp-section-header">
        <h2 class="lp-section-heading">Laptop Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="lp-section-subheading">Common questions about laptop repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lp-faq-list">
        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">How long does a laptop screen replacement take in Winnipeg?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Most laptop screen replacements are completed within 1–2 hours at our Winnipeg St. Vital location when parts are in stock. For less common laptop models or premium display panels, we may need to order a part — we'll give you an estimated wait time when you contact us.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">Can you upgrade my laptop's RAM and SSD in Winnipeg?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — we perform SSD and RAM upgrades on most laptops at our Winnipeg location. An SSD upgrade is the single most impactful performance improvement you can make on an older laptop — replacing a spinning hard drive with an NVMe SSD can make a years-old machine boot in seconds and feel completely new again.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">My laptop won't turn on. Can you fix it in Winnipeg?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — we diagnose and repair laptop power failures ranging from simple battery or charger problems through to complex motherboard-level faults. We perform component-level diagnostics and micro-soldering for charging IC failures, power delivery faults, and display connection issues that most Winnipeg laptop shops won't attempt.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">Do you repair Chromebooks in Winnipeg?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — we service all Chromebook brands including Asus, Acer, Lenovo, HP, Dell, and Google Pixelbook at our Winnipeg location. Chromebook screen replacements and keyboard repairs are the most common Chromebook fixes we perform.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">Is it worth repairing my old laptop?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>It depends on the repair cost versus the laptop's current value and remaining useful life — a battery replacement or SSD upgrade on a well-built 5-year-old laptop almost always makes sense, while a motherboard repair on a budget 7-year-old machine may not. We provide a free diagnostic and honest assessment at our Winnipeg location before you commit to anything.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">Do you repair gaming laptops in Winnipeg?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — we repair Asus ROG, Acer Nitro and Predator, Lenovo Legion, HP Omen, Dell Alienware, Razer Blade, and MSI gaming laptops at our Winnipeg shop. Gaming laptops frequently need thermal paste replacement and heatsink cleaning due to the high sustained loads they run under — overheating is by far the most common gaming laptop repair we perform.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">Can you fix a laptop with a broken or loose hinge?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — hinge repairs are a common laptop fix we perform at our Winnipeg location. Loose or broken hinges often cause the screen to wobble or crack the plastic chassis around the hinge mounting points. We repair hinges and reinforce or replace the chassis damage they cause on all laptop brands.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">Do you repair laptop charging ports in Winnipeg?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — we repair both DC barrel jack charging ports on older laptops and USB-C charging ports on modern thin-and-light models at our Winnipeg shop. Most charging port repairs are completed same-day and we always test the full charging chain before recommending a port replacement.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">Do you offer free laptop diagnostics in Winnipeg?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — we provide free diagnostics on all laptops at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. Walk in any time during business hours and we'll assess your laptop and give you a clear upfront quote before starting any repair — no obligation and no fee for the diagnostic itself.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary class="lp-faq-question">Do you repair laptops in Thompson, MB?</summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts laptop repairs Monday through Saturday 10AM–6PM. For screen replacements or less common brands, calling ahead helps us confirm parts availability before your visit.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
